## 4. Visual system & design tokens

All values below are the locked *starting* tokens. Exact hex can be fine-tuned in-build, but
the intent (warm off-white base, warm-grey neutrals, one deep muted teal, humanist type,
calm motion) is fixed. Express every value as a token (CSS custom property + Tailwind theme
entry); nothing hardcoded in components.

### Colour — warm, light, one accent used sparingly
```
--bg            #F8F5EF   /* warm off-white "paper" base — NOT clinical white, NOT beige */
--surface       #FFFFFF   /* cards/raised surfaces, or a hair warmer than bg */
--text          #2A2723   /* warm near-black — primary text */
--text-secondary #6B655C  /* warm grey — supporting text */
--text-muted    #9A9389   /* warm grey — hints, captions, tags */
--border        rgba(42,39,35,0.10)   /* warm hairline */
--border-strong rgba(42,39,35,0.18)
--accent        #1E5F57   /* deep, muted pine teal — the ONE accent */
--accent-hover  #174A44
--accent-tint   rgba(30,95,87,0.08)   /* focus/hover washes */
```
**Accent budget — the accent is a guest, not a resident.** Teal appears only on: the résumé
button, links, and at most one hover state. Everywhere else is warm-neutral. If teal shows up
in 5+ places, it's wrong.

**Contrast is non-negotiable** (it's the a11y claim): every text/background pair must pass WCAG
AA minimum. Verify `--text-secondary` and `--text-muted` on `--bg`, and teal-as-link on `--bg`,
during build.

### Typography — humanist warmth (display), invisible clarity (body)
- **Display** (headline, section headings): **Bricolage Grotesque** — humanist warmth, subtle
  character, still calm. Weights 400/500/600.
- **Body** (descriptions, UI, everything read): **Inter** — max legibility/accessibility, gets
  out of the way. Weights 400/500.
- **Mono** (tags, small technical labels only): **JetBrains Mono** — a quiet engineered wink
  reinforcing the measurement identity.
- Two-face rule: display + body do the work; mono is a detail accent only. Load all three via
  `next/font` (self-host, subset, `font-display: swap`) to keep character *and* the Lighthouse
  score — no layout shift.

### Spacing — 8px scale, balanced rhythm
Scale: `8 / 16 / 24 / 32 / 48 / 64`. **Loose between major sections** (each section is its own
moment and breathes), **snug within components** (card padding, element gaps). Balanced, not
airy, not cramped.

### Layout container
Contained, centred column with a max-width (~1080–1120px) and side padding (24px mobile,
scaling up on larger screens). The *same* container governs every section — that shared
column is the page's visual through-line. Never let content run edge-to-edge on wide screens.

### Motion feel + easing (motion is central — this is the personality)
- **Feel:** calm, long, settling. Gentle fades and short rises for entrances; smooth scrubbed
  scroll effects; **no** fly-ins, no bounce, no snap. Confident enough not to show off.
- **House easing (locked, single curve everywhere):** `cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)`.
  Store as `--ease` and reference it on every transition/reveal/hover/GSAP tween. Nothing ever
  falls back to the browser default `ease`.

### Responsive breakpoints
Mobile-first. Primary breakpoints: `md` 768px, `lg` 1024px. Every section's mobile behaviour is
specified per-section in §6.

