## 9. Definition of done (quality bar — itself part of the work-sample)

- [ ] Lighthouse 100 / 100 / 100 / 100 (perf / a11y / best-practices / SEO), screenshotted
- [ ] Keyboard-navigable end to end; visible focus on every interactive element
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected on **every** animation, **and** the footer toggle
      genuinely disables motion
- [ ] Smooth on a real mid-range phone; no scroll jank; CLS ≈ 0
- [ ] Contrast passes WCAG AA on every text/bg pair (warm neutrals + teal verified)
- [ ] Accent used sparingly (résumé + links + ≤1 hover) — a guest, not a resident
- [ ] One house easing curve (`--ease`) on every motion; nothing on default `ease`
- [ ] Fonts via `next/font`, subset, `display: swap` — no layout shift
- [ ] Résumé one click from both nav and footer
- [ ] Featured CLP card fully clickable (mouse/tap/keyboard); hover overlay is enhancement only
- [ ] Three supporting cards are static, not clickable, and don't *look* clickable
- [ ] Differentiators honest and demonstrated, not asserted
- [ ] CLP shipped as centrepiece, spec-tagged, clean-room, with its own brand identity
- [ ] No dangling GSAP/ScrollTrigger/Lenis instances across route changes

