## 10. Guardrails

- **Restraint is the brief.** "Too cluttered" is the failure mode. Default to the quieter option.
- **Demonstrate, don't assert** — every element shows the claim rather than stating it.
- **Honesty/scoping** — no overclaims; client work is describable but not publishable; the CLP
  is clearly a spec built on real, honestly-framed experience.
- **The a11y claim must be true** — if any motion can't be made reduced-motion-safe, fix the
  motion, don't drop the fallback.
- **AI-assisted workflow is a strength** — this build (chat for design thinking, Claude Code for
  the build) is exactly the daily-AI-tooling habit the JD wants; be ready to describe it.

