## 11. Step-wise build plan

Ordered, dependency-aware. Run it top to bottom. Within each phase, follow the **default mode
from §2**: hand Tarun one small action at a time, wait, verify, then the next. Static structure
before motion, frame before CLP, so nothing is built on shifting ground. Each phase ends at a
verify checkpoint — don't advance until it passes.

**Phase 0 — Setup & live pipeline (day one)**
- Scaffold Next.js (App Router) + TS + Tailwind.
- Public GitHub repo, clean commits.
- Connect Vercel, deploy the blank app, enable Vercel Analytics.
- ✅ Checkpoint: a blank page is live on a `*.vercel.app` URL and redeploys on push. (Custom
  domain can wait for Phase 7.)

**Phase 1 — Tokens & primitives**
- Encode every §4 token into `tailwind.config` + CSS vars: colours, 8px spacing scale, the
  `--ease` curve, radii.
- Load fonts via `next/font` (Bricolage Grotesque, Inter, JetBrains Mono) — subset, `swap`.
- Build the shared primitives: the max-width `Container`, the `Button` (résumé/filled variant),
  base typography.
- ✅ Checkpoint: a throwaway test page proves tokens, fonts, container, and button all render.

**Phase 2 — Frame shell (chrome, no content yet)**
- Root layout, shared container, base bg/text tokens.
- Sticky nav (wordmark, quiet links, filled résumé button, condense-on-scroll, anchor links).
- Footer (three links, repeated résumé button, reduced-motion toggle placeholder).
- ✅ Checkpoint: nav sticks/condenses, anchors scroll, footer lays out, all responsive.

**Phase 3 — Frame content, static (no motion)**
- Hero (weighty left headline, subline, contained column, fold-bait — static).
- Selected work: featured CLP card (fully clickable, text-left/preview-right, mobile stack) +
  three static, non-clickable cards (heading + description + tag row).
- Differentiators band (no header, two columns, calm, generous space).
- ✅ Checkpoint: the whole frame reads correctly and responsively with zero animation.

**Phase 4 — Signature + motion layer (frame)**
- Install GSAP + `@gsap/react`, Lenis, Framer Motion.
- Scroll-progress indicator (whisper-thin teal), reduced-motion toggle (real: toggles motion +
  honours OS `prefers-reduced-motion`).
- Entrance reveals (fade + short rise, `--ease`), hero background motion behind the overlay,
  hover micro-interactions. Wire Lenis to ScrollTrigger.
- ✅ Checkpoint: motion is calm and smooth, reduced-motion path works, no dangling instances on
  route change.

**Phase 5 — A11y + performance pass (frame)**
- Keyboard nav end-to-end, focus-visible, ARIA, contrast checks on every pair.
- `next/image`, lazy-load below fold, code-split, CLS ≈ 0.
- ✅ Checkpoint: Lighthouse 100/100/100/100 on the frame, screenshotted.

**Phase 6 — The CLP (`/work/clp`) — its own build (§7)**
- New route; its own TIMBRE tokens (`--tb-*`) and fonts (Syne + Manrope); its own `--tb-ease`.
- Build the six sections static first, then layer motion: scrubbed hero → pinned/scrubbed
  promise → parallax → sticky features → variant carousel (signature) → closing.
- Reduced-motion fallback on every effect; a11y + perf pass; Lighthouse 100s on the route.
- ✅ Checkpoint: CLP is a complete, accessible, performant scroll experience, spec-tagged, with a
  back-to-portfolio link.

**Phase 7 — Content, polish, ship**
- Real copy (hero, the three project descriptions, the two differentiator sentences), résumé PDF
  in place, OG image + SEO meta.
- Custom domain: paste Vercel's two nameservers into Porkbun; confirm HTTPS issues.
- Make the GitHub repo presentable (this site's code lives there).
